<textList name="TEXT_SCRAPPER_OUTPOST">
    <text>A Scrapper Outpost has been constructed in this sector. A steady flow of activity is coming and going from the station, however, no signals are being publically broadcast, indicating this to be a research or military facility.</text>
    <text>Within this sector lies a formidable Scrapper Outpost. The constant flurry of activity hints at the outpost's significance, yet the absence of any public broadcasts raises intriguing questions about its true purpose, possibly pointing towards secretive research endeavors or covert military operations.</text>
    <text>The beacon transmitting the location of the facility is a mystery. The Scrapper Outpost in this region is not boardcasting public signals on it's own, yet it would seem that they are inviting ships in with the beacon transmitting a signal.</text>
    <text>Amidst this sector, an imposing Scrapper Outpost commands attention, its presence marked by a continuous ebb and flow of activity. The absence of public broadcasts veils the outpost's true nature, leaving room for speculation.</text>
    <text>A formidable Scrapper Outpost has taken root in this sector. Could it serve as a covert hub for cutting-edge research or as a strategic military stronghold, concealed from prying eyes?</text>
</textList>

<event name="SCRAPPER_OUTPOST">
	<text load="TEXT_SCRAPPER_OUTPOST" />
	<ship load="SHIP_SCRAPPER_OUTPOST" hostile="false" />
	<changeBackground>BACK_SECTOR_SCRAPPER</changeBackground>
	<preventQuest />
	<beaconType id="map_icon_triangle_yellow" global="false">
		<color r="255" g="0" b="255" a="1" />
	</beaconType>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Engage the outpost.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It's better to shoot first and ask questions later.</text>
			<ship hostile="true" />
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK" />
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the outpost.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Assuming this is a military facility, it would be heavily armed and very difficult to breach. It would be better to avoid conflict and leave the area.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something on-board the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK" />
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event />
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_SCRAPPER_MILITARY" blue="true">
		<text>(Military Scrapper) Your scrapper taps your shoulder and requests a word.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You see what's up.
			"THIS STATION IS A MILITARY BASE! SERVED HERE! BELIEVE ARMS MANUFACTURING OR STORAGE! LOTS OF SCRAP! LOTS OF GUARDS!"
			They should at you with their typical cadance. Knowing that the outpost is indeed a military base is good to know and the appeal of raiding an arms manufactury is tempting. You ask your scrapper what they can do.
			"POSE AS TRANSFER! RAID THE ARMORY! RETURN! NO ONE WILL NOTICE!!!"</text>
			<choice>
				<text>You see nothing wrong with this plan at all.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You approach the outpost and are hailed shortly after turning your ship towards the outpost. You advise them that you are transporting an incoming transfer. They shout something about a requisition number.
					"#584154!!!" The scrapper shouts over your shoulder before you have a chance to even consider what to do. The voice from the outpost accepts the number, and your scrapper is teleported from the bridge. With the 'Transfer' complete, you return the ship to the beacon, emulating a departure.
					</text>
					<choice>
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>A few minutes later you receive a communication from your scrapper indicating that they were successful in raiding the armory and are ready to be extracted. However, they will notice the teleportation, as well as you getting close enough, and also the scrapper who raided their armory is not necessarily the sneakiest.
							Something tells you this plan was not well thought out, but it is in motion now!
							You do a flyby of the outpost and beam your scrapper aboard as well as the weapon and scrap they stole.
							As anticipated, the outpost is now on high alert, and a fight is inevitable.</text>
							<choice>
								<text>Prepare for battle!</text>
								<event>
									<ship hostile="true" />
									<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event load="COMBAT_CHECK" />
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>This is a bad idea. Shoot them.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It's better to shoot first and ask questions later.</text>
					<ship hostile="true" />
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK" />
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>This is a bad idea. Let's just leave.</text>
				<event>
					<text>This is a military facility, it's better to leave it be. </text>
					<choice>
						<text>Do something on-board the ship.</text>
						<event load="STORAGE_CHECK" />
					</choice>
					<choice>
						<text>Do nothing.</text>
						<event />
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

