<event name="SCRAPPER_ENCOUNTER_SHOP">
	<text>A scrapper vessel is in this sector. It's broadcasting a signal simply asking for scrap. Perhaps they mean to trade?</text>
	<ship load="SCRAPPER_SHOP" hostile="false" />
	<beaconType id="map_icon_store_scrapper" global="true">
		<color r="255" g="65" b="254" a="1" />
	</beaconType>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack them!</text>
		<event>
			<text>"EXCUSE ME?!? WE WILL STRIP THE SCRAP FROM YOUR BLOATED CARCASS!"
			It seems a boarding party has entered your ship. Maybe they had a super shield bypass?</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<boarders min="2" max="2" class="scrapper_soldier" />
			<boarders min="1" max="1" class="scrapper_medic" />
			<boarders min="1" max="1" class="scrapper_heavy" />
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK" />
			</choice>
		</event>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Hail them and see if they would like to trade.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"WE NEED SCRAP!" </text>
			<store>SCRAPPER_NORMAL_STORE</store>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="LIST_CREW_SCRAPPER" blue="true" hidden="true">
		<text>Your scrapper waves his hands and sends a signal to the scrapper ship; "C0UPON COD3!!!" He types in a short code and you notice the store prices drop!</text>
		<store>SCRAPPER_NORMAL_STORE_DISCOUNT</store>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="SCRAPPER_ENCOUNTER_SUPPORT">
	<text>A scrapper support ship is in this sector. It seems to not notice you, or it does and it does not care.</text>
	<ship load="TC_SCRAPPER_SUPPORT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack the ship before it gets any bright ideas.</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK" />
			</choice>
	</choice>
	<choice req="LIST_CREW_SCRAPPER" blue="true" hidden="true">
		<text>Consult your scrapper.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Your scrapper advises you that the support ship seems to be lost. It is supposed to be with others, as part of a fleet, but this one is alone. They may need help but may find themselves unable to ask. 
			Your scrapper tells you that it would be good to hail them, as scrappers typically only care about 1 thing and are generally not overly hostile to aliens or humans.</text>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="true">
				<text>Hail the scrapper support ship and offer assistance.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Scrapper captain responds to you with a bit of a flustered tone, "HAPPY T0 S33 FL3SHY C@PTA!N WE ARE IN NEED 0F R3PA!RS!! C@N Y0U SPARE SCR@P!!???"</text>
					<text>It seems that the scrapper does indeed only have 1 thing on its mind.</text>
					<choice req="LIST_CREW_SCRAPPER" blue="true">
						<text>Ask your Scrapper what they think.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your Scrapper tells you that the Scrapper captain sounds genuine, but you can never be too sure since, of course, he's asking for Scrap.
							But if you are able to help someone, don't you think you should?</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Transfer the Scrapper some scrap to help facilitate their repairs.</text>
									<event>
										<text>You send over the scrap...</text>
										<item_modify> 
											<item type="scrap" min="-35" max="-35"/>
										</item_modify>
										<choice hidden="true">
											<text>Continue...</text>
										</choice>
											<event>
												<text>"THANK Y0U CAPTAIN! WE CAN OPERATE OUR ENGINES AGAIN!! TAKE FANCY MACHINE WE FIND"</text>
												<autoReward level="HIGH">augment</autoReward>
											</event>
									</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Order your crew to prepare for battle!</text>
					<event>
						<ship hostile="true"/>
						<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK" />
					</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Leave them alone.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Leave them alone.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>

